parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the traction control, brake service, and steering lights to illuminate on the dashboard, leading to potential loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Illumination of traction control
brake service
and steering lights on the dashboard
inability to stop the vehicle
brake pedal making contact with the floorboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective brake rotors can cause the vehicle to experience brake failure, leading to potential loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rusting and warping of brake rotors
frequent replacement of brake rotors
brake pedal making contact with the floorboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake failure can cause the vehicle to experience sudden acceleration or inability to stop, leading to potential loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
inability to stop the vehicle
brake pedal making contact with the floorboard
failure to engage brakes when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed sensor can cause the vehicle to experience sudden acceleration or brake failure, leading to potential loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
inability to stop the vehicle
failure to engage brakes when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when applying the brakes
especially when parking in angle or off-camber spaces. The engine RPM remains high
and the vehicle may accelerate to high speeds without the driver's input. In some cases
the vehicle may be difficult to bring under control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty sensors or wiring issues can cause unintended acceleration, making it difficult to control the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The engine RPM remains high
and the vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly. In some cases
the vehicle may be difficult to bring under control. Frayed or damaged wires may be found
and repairs may not be effective in resolving the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Traction control system malfunctions can cause unintended acceleration, making it difficult to control the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when parking in angle or off-camber spaces. The engine RPM remains high
and the vehicle may accelerate to high speeds without the driver's input. In some cases
the vehicle may be difficult to bring under control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning crank sensor can cause the engine to lose power, leading to a loss of steering and braking, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls intermittently
especially at high speeds
and may lose power without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing damage to other engine components.
symptoms: The "Check Engine Coolant" warning indicator illuminates on the instrument panel
and the engine may overheat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch cylinder wires can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks, especially if the vehicle stalls while in motion.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the starter break is disabled
the message "Wait 3 minutes and restart the car" appears
intermittent stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of Sensors A and B can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to potential safety risks, especially if the vehicle stalls while in motion.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the sensor loses its signal
intermittent stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor visibility of the electronic gauges on the instrument panel can cause the driver to be unaware of important vehicle information, leading to potential safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument panel gauges are not visible or difficult to read
especially under certain lighting conditions
the backlighting is not adjustable to a brightness that can be easily seen
the pointers are dark red
narrow
or small and hard to see at a glance.
